From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native ssao_blur in-frame
 SMART blur slice replacement

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040 (the branch-HEAD gpu_culling tail plus the
tonemap rd_native slice). This is the second Route B REAL replacement pass:
Route B drives the Rurix ssao_blur kernel as a first-class in-frame
RenderingDevice compute dispatch for the SMART edge-aware blur slices,
instead of the out-of-frame rxgd shim bridge, and when it records the native
Godot SMART blur dispatch for that slice is genuinely skipped (no scaffold
clear, unlike patch 0016).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_ssao_blur_rd_native(int64_t compute_list, RID source_slice,
  RID dest_slice, Size2i slice_size, float edge_sharpness,
  float half_screen_pixel_size_x, float half_screen_pixel_size_y). It takes
  the Godot ComputeListID of the ALREADY-OPEN generate_ssao compute list
  (SSAO opens one list around the whole gather/blur/interleave chain, so
  rd_native must NOT begin/end its own) plus Godot RID handles (not native
  ID3D12Resource* handles like the shim-path try_record_ssao_blur) so the
  module can build an RD uniform set and record one slice dispatch. Base
  returns false, so hooks that do not override it keep the native path.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings,
  independent of the four existing ssao_blur shim settings (untouched):
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/ssao_blur/backend (int, default 0;
  0=disabled / 1=shim / 2=rd_native) and
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/ssao_blur/rd_container_path (string, default
  ""). Defaults keep the RD-native path disabled.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_ssao_blur_rd_native
  override. Lazily builds the compute pipeline once (FileAccess reads the
  Rurix container -> shader_create_from_bytecode -> compute_pipeline_create,
  latching rd_native_ssao_blur_load_failed on any failure so it is not
  retried per frame), runs a usage-bits preflight (source SAMPLING_BIT, dest
  STORAGE_BIT), binds t0=source slice (SRV/UNIFORM_TYPE_TEXTURE) and
  u0=dest slice (UAV/UNIFORM_TYPE_IMAGE) via UniformSetCacheRD, packs the
  28-byte b0 push constants ([i64 slice_width, i64 slice_height,
  f32 edge_sharpness, f32 half_screen_pixel_size_x,
  f32 half_screen_pixel_size_y]), and records a ceil(size/8) dispatch onto
  the caller's compute list. No submit()/sync() (a local-RD-only concept).
  The one-shot RXGD_RD_NATIVE_SSAO_BLUR active marker is emitted via
  print_verbose when the pipeline is first built (not per-frame).
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/effects/ss_effects.cpp: in the Edge-Aware
  Blur loop, backend == 2 runs the rd_native gate BEFORE the shim gate, and
  ONLY for the SMART blur pipeline (blur_pipeline == SSAO_BLUR_PASS_SMART);
  a successful record skips both the shim gate and the native SMART blur
  dispatch for that slice. backend != 2 leaves the pre-existing shim/native
  chain byte-for-byte unchanged.

Fail-closed everywhere: with the default backend == 0 (and empty container
path), rd_native is never engaged and the native Godot SSAO blur renders.
The kernel covers only the MODE_SMART single-slice edge-aware blur subset
(no very-low/WIDE blur pipelines, no 4-slice fusion, no interleave), so
only the SMART blur slices route through rd_native and the rest stay native.
RXGD_ABI_VERSION is unchanged (this path does not touch the C ABI struct
layout and sets no RxGdCaps.flags bit; rd_native is bridge-independent). No
performance claim is made.
